&gt;
&gt; Hi Markus,
&gt;
&gt; There’s an org.archive.crawler.prefetch.QuotaEnforcer class; setting 
&gt; the property “serverMaxFetchSuccesses” or “serverMaxFetchResponses” to 
&gt; a integer value (depending on whether you want to count HTTP errors):
&gt;
&gt; &lt;bean id=&quot;quotaEnforcer&quot; 
&gt; class=&quot;org.archive.crawler.prefetch.QuotaEnforcer&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt; &lt;property name=&quot;serverMaxFetchSuccesses&quot; value=&quot;100&quot;/&gt;
&gt;
&gt; &lt;/bean&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Add this to your Fetch chain:
&gt;
&gt; &lt;bean id=&quot;fetchProcessors&quot; class=&quot;org.archive.modules.FetchChain&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt; &lt;property name=&quot;processors&quot;&gt;
&gt;
&gt; &lt;list&gt;
&gt;
&gt; &lt;!-- enforce per-host quotas... --&gt;
&gt;
&gt;                                 &lt;ref bean=&quot;quotaEnforcer&quot;/&gt;
&gt;
&gt; …
&gt;
